The [Assumption of the Virgin](/Assumption_of_the_Virgin_(Botticini)), a masterpiece by [Francesco Botticini](/Francesco_Botticini) painted between 1475 and 1476, now residing in the National Gallery, London, offers a visual representation of this intricate celestial structure. It depicts no fewer than three distinct [hierarchies](/Hierarchy_of_angels) and nine separate orders of angels, each imbued with unique characteristics and responsibilities. It’s a rather ambitious piece, attempting to capture the divine order in pigment.

